						               													<description>Overview: Take on the role of a viking captain and steer your ship through the sea, past difficult navigable sea, ice and privateers.&amp;#10;Discover islands and trade goods or transporting oldest to fulfill your orders and collect gold and silver.&amp;#10;Upgrade your ship with different extensions and hire new viking crew members.&amp;#10;Furthermore be beware of your takers, who will make your journey as hard as possible.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game-description:&amp;#10;The players control a viking ship. At the start of the game every player gets one ship card, some order cards and event cards.&amp;#10;The order cards are the goals, that every player has to accomplish to win the game! There are several kind of order cards, for example: gather goods and bring them to a specific harbor or transport a viking and so on. Every card gives a player some vicotry points and if a player has more than twelve points at the end of a round the game ends.&amp;#10;The game is played in clockwise direction. A player can do three actions during his turn. The actions are:&amp;#10;1.    Catch fish (if you are on a game-tile with fish)&amp;#10;2.    Rotate your ship one tile and move (or just move on tile)&amp;#10;3.    Rotate your ship in the other direction&amp;#10;4.    Lay in on a harbor&amp;#10;5.    Gerate two silver (oversee trade, only once each turn!)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In every round the players can also bribe some independent vikings to mug another player, if the black ship catches a player.&amp;#10;Forthermore the players have to expand their viking ship, for example to transport more goods or to sail faster and so on.&amp;#10;One game turn consists of: &amp;#10;1.    Every player do actions clockwise&amp;#10;2.    Bribe the Freebooter&amp;#10;3.    Every player do actions clockwise&amp;#10;4.    Give out some goods, vikings (for transport) to the islands and their markets&amp;#10;At least, player can buy and use event cards to manuipulate for example the island markets, the freebooter or other player ships.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
